{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1a5baa6e-864f-4489-817d-804323aa26ec","content":"**Starting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0.0, VSTest support was removed by default.**\n\nMSTest.Sdk 4.x exclusively uses **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** (the new `dotnet test` integration) and no longer ships the VSTest adapter/bridge. That's why `vstest.console` can't discover your tests — the VSTest adapter assemblies are simply not in the output.\n\n### How to fix\n\nYou have two options:\n\n**Option 1 (recommended) — Stop using `vstest.console`:**\n\nReplace your CI command:\n\n```diff\n- vstest.console MyTests.dll\n+ dotnet test MyTests.csproj\n```\n\n`dotnet test` in .NET 8+ natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\n**Option 2 — Re-enable VSTest compatibility:**\n\nAdd this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>false</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nand add the VSTest bridge package:\n\n```xml\n<ItemGroup>\n  <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest.Sdk.VSTestBridge\" Version=\"4.1.0\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\nOption 1 is the intended path forward — Microsoft.Testing.Platform replaces VSTest as the default runner in MSTest 4.x.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3c68cf6a-bfca-4f8e-9eeb-9c86555cebfa","outputTokens":364,"requestId":"5C22:28F9DD:4DF4CF:61313A:69F565C9"},"id":"48484d8b-f98c-489a-b310-fe2fe539d1e0","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:47:47.440Z","parentId":"6a88a5cd-d4c3-4269-b726-875cfa7f42f8"}
